This place is on the 3rd floor of the outdoor portion of the mall. Google maps will mislead you and put you on the Macys side if the mall, but you want the opposite side. The restaurant is in a quieter portion of the mall where one can hear the music downstairs,  but its muted enough to enjoy conversation. We started in the front patio area that had a high ceiling and was divided from.the mall by hanging platters and crab traps, so it was both airy and private. Service was efficient yet very pleasant and personable.  We had the Skiff seafood platter, plus two cocktails: Better Mules and Gardens and (I think) the Smokey Mistress. Both were sizable and well-constructed. Delicious.  The platter included oysters, crab, lobster and shrimp, all on a bed of ice along with 5 dipping sauces. All were perfectly prepared,  and the shrimp were a standout - we ordered a few more of those. So fresh and sweet.

Here goes (please bear with me; this will be a long review): I'm not a fan of leaving companies one star reviews, but this restaurant is the exception. I have a very restrictive diet (due to allergies, I cannot have seafood, primarily). Frequently, especially at seafood restaurants, I have to "special order" dishes... And sometimes, that means I have to request plates off of the kid's menu, because it is the safest option for me. This has NEVER been a problem ANYWHERE, and I have had these problems my whole life. Tonight, I was with a wedding party at Herringbone. When I went to order, I requested chicken from the kid's menu. The waiter was very rude about this, and he said he would have to "speak to the chef because the kid's menu is for KIDS not adults." When he served our food, he made sure to tell me again: "This is a one time thing. This is not an adult meal. This is for kids. We won't do this again."  Now, for some context. The party I was with spent over a thousand dollars (yes, $1000) on our meal for about 10 people. For the waiter to be so rude and to make a big deal about my ordering a meal that they offer -- this is beyond me.  (Also, I'd like to say that what I did end up getting was terrible.) I am contacting management as well.

We were excited to eat at this restaurant.  On entering there is a plaque announcing best new restaurant 2019.  Promising to be a great experience right?  Unfortunately ours was only so, so.  Absolutely the decor is exquisite!!  Perfectly designed aesthetics.  The lighting was beautiful, beyond the fixtures, the lighting effects provide a beautiful dimly lit ambiance.  The music was nice, although the restaurant was loud and at times hard to hear the music.  The service was ok, not the best and not the worst.  The food and drinks however... unfortunately disappointing.  We googled pics of the food ahead of time and so we knew what to expect. We ordered the whole fish, pink snapper.   The review pics showed it to be standing and a beautiful color of darkish pink/salmon.  Our fish arrived laying down as though it fell over and a unexpected grayish/white color.  It was appreciated that the waitress disassembled the fish at our table.  However, more than the appearance being disappointing, was the flavor.   We expected it as described by our waitress.  Crisp and crunchy on the outside and moist and soft on the inside  Outside, yes, as described. Inside, dry and lacking of flavor and very little meat.  For $55 this plate was disappointing in presentation and flavor.  The positives were definitely the ceviche tostadas and the green lip muscles.   The drink menu  had some great  drink titles, that also read well in terms of ingredients.  However we felt these failed to wow us also.  Our meal, with tip was approximately $200.  We are not afraid to spend the money, though we expect an experience in return.   We both left disappointed.  A beautiful restaurant is only as good as it's food and beverages in the end.  But ultimately I dine to enjoy the food and beverages.

To start, I would just like to say that the first impression and walking in experience was very nice. The combination of different décor styles using a drift wood look, tropical plants, other coastal living accents was very well incorporated in the restaurant.  Service was very friendly and sincere from the start and all the way to the finish. Everyone working seemed genuine and happy to be there as well as egger to please. Our server was very attentive and was always checking to see if everything was okay, although she seemed to always ask how we were doing at the moment we had food in our mouths, but that is everywhere I guess.  LOL  The oysters were very tasty, but I think the person doing the shucking needs a bit more instructions on how to do it a bit more cleanly.  I kept getting oyster shells in my bites, but it was forgiven with the quality and flavor of the oysters.  The Smoked Trout Caesar was excellent.  Ordered it as a split to share.  It was the perfect cleanse after the oysters to the main course. Ordered two mains.  The Hokkaido Scallops were excellent.  Tasty and cooked to perfection.  Great flavor and tenderness.  Only disappointment was they looked like they were plated like an appetizer. Would have liked a bit more of the bamboo rice that they were bedded on.  For the Tomahawk Porkchop, that was the big disappointment. It was a very sad looking, little bone-in porkchop that I could have gotten at any grocery store and not really of any notable flavor or outstanding quality. I would pass at $38.  The Mango Beer was a tasty delight for a lighter beer that went well with the meal through the desert.  Not heavy or to light. Flavors most would like.  It is located in the International Market Place 3rd floor, so the majority of the customers were tourists.  That being said, we noticed more children then normal.  There were some fussy ones, but being a fairly open restaurant, the crying and squawking tolerable for the most part.  One big regret was that after we were finished, we saw someone ordered the whole fish at the table next to us.  It was beautiful.  That would have been a winner for us.  So that being said, we will be back to try the dish we missed.

We absolutely love this place. The menu is simple and the atmosphere is amazing. Definitely get the seafood tower. We've gone here for dinner on our last two anniversaries and will come back again. It's a little pricey but worth it. The manager comes around and talks to the partons and you just feel welcome. Must go place if you're in Waikiki.

This is one of my favorite spots in downtown Waikiki.  The food and drinks are excellent.  Occasionally, the staff is slow - on one visit, I sat at the bar for nearly 10 minutes and was seconds away from walking out when another patron pointed me out to the two bartenders, both of whom had walked past me multiple times without acknowledging me.  However, the other experiences I've had have made up for it.  Having moved to Oahu from Southern California, I often miss the "Coastal" Californian cuisine of fresh fish, farm grown vegetables...etc.  The snapper at Herringbone is superb and was prepared perfectly.  The cocktails are unique and inventive.  And the atmosphere is relaxed, chill, and soothing.  Trust me, it's well worth a visit - and the price.  Parking at the International Marketplace will be validated by the restaurant.
